  "text": "Modeling. With the black hole masses and bolometric luminosities given in Tables 2 and 3 , we proceed to PRT-simulations. The main idea comes to solving an inverse problem. Figure 5 : The BH / ⊙ -(5100Å)/ ⊙ relation on logarithmic scales for 34 objects from [CITATION_1] . The solid line is the best fits to data of samples. Namely, by reiterating integrations of the state equations of SPC-configurations we determine those required central values of particle concentration (0) and ID-field (0), for which the total mass of configuration obtained after integration is equal to the black hole mass estimated from observations. Among all the integral characteristics, the radius is also computed, which is used to calculate BH . The results are summed up in Table 3 . The obtained PRT values are ranging from Log( BH /yr) ≃ 9.89 to 10.43 for the masses Log( BH / ⊙ ) ≃ 7.77 to 8.18 of central black holes in 5 nuclear components of the samples of Mrk 261/262 and Mrk 266. Figure 6 plots the PRT-mass relation on logarithmic scales.",
